---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Connections">
  <h1>Connections</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">Data sources and destinations — databases, APIs, cloud warehouses, and files.</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>A <strong>connection</strong> represents a data source or destination. Connections store encrypted credentials and configuration needed to access external systems. They are reusable across multiple uploads and pipelines.</p>
  <p>Direction (source, destination, or both) is <strong>automatically determined</strong> from the connection type. Databases and warehouses can be used as both source and destination. APIs and files are source-only.</p>

  <h3>Properties</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>name</code></td><td>Display name (e.g., "Production Postgres")</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>connection_type</code></td><td>Type of system (see supported types below)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>config</code></td><td>Connection credentials (encrypted at rest with Fernet)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>freshness_config</code></td><td>Optional source freshness checks (warn/error thresholds)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Supported Types</h2>

  <h3>Databases (source & destination)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>postgres</code></td><td>PostgreSQL 12+</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>mysql</code></td><td>MySQL 5.7+</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>mssql</code></td><td>SQL Server 2016+</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>sqlite</code></td><td>Local SQLite files</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>clickhouse</code></td><td>ClickHouse 21+ (supports clustered ReplicatedMergeTree)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>duckdb</code></td><td>DuckDB (embedded analytics)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Cloud Warehouses (source & destination)</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
